org.coniks.coniks_common

Class ServerErr

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.coniks.coniks_common.ServerErr

  • public final class ServerErr
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines constants representing the types of errors that the server may return to a client.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int INTERNAL_SERVER_ERR
      Indicates that an error internal to the server occurred.
      static int MALFORMED_CLIENT_MSG_ERR
      Indicates that the message the server received from the client was malformed.
      static int MALFORMED_SERVER_MSG_ERR
      Indicates that the message the client received from the server was malformed.
      static int NAME_EXISTS_ERR
      Indicates that the name the client tried to register with the server already exists and could not be registered.
      static int NAME_NOT_FOUND_ERR
      Indicates that the server could not find the name the client tried to lookup.
      static int SERVER_ERR
      Indicates a generic server error.
      static int SIGNED_CHANGE_VERIF_ERR
      Indicates that the server could not verify the signed change message received by the client.
      static int SUCCESS
      Indicates that the server returned no error.
